# Smart Contract Standards

## Environment

- Solidity `0.8.26`, EVM version `cancun`, optimizer runs: 200
- Hardhat 2.22 + `@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox`
- OpenZeppelin Contracts v5
- Target chains: Polygon Amoy (chainId 80002) / Polygon PoS (chainId 137)

## Contract Overview

| Contract | Responsibility |
|----------|---------------|
| `AccessPassNFT.sol` | Access-right ERC-721: mint, consume, pause, 24h cooldown, non-transferable |
| `DepositVault.sol` | JPYC escrow: hold, capture, release |
| `ComputeMarket.sol` | Compute marketplace: node registration, job state machine, 75/25 revenue split |
| `MockERC20.sol` | JPYC mock for testing |

## Coding Conventions

- Use OpenZeppelin's `Ownable`, `ReentrancyGuard`, `Pausable` standard modules
- Event naming: past-tense verbs (`PassMinted`, `JobCompleted`)
- Use custom errors instead of require strings
- JPYC ERC-20 address is injected at deployment, never hardcoded

## Testing

- Framework: Mocha + Chai (Hardhat built-in)
- Test files located at `packages/contracts/test/`
- Run: `npm run test -w @nodestay/contracts`
- Coverage: `npm run coverage -w @nodestay/contracts`

## Deployment

```bash
cd packages/contracts
npx hardhat compile
npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.ts --network amoy
```

Environment variables (`.env`): `DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY`, `AMOY_RPC_URL`, `POLYGON_RPC_URL`, `POLYGONSCAN_API_KEY`, `PLATFORM_FEE_RECIPIENT`, `JPYC_TOKEN_ADDRESS`
